    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The right or condition of vsible power or control over real or other property, defined by the intention to use or to hold it against others, typically as distinct from, or at least not synonymous with, lawful ownership.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
